—ЩNarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/mktemp.mdЩ@f532bb8038b7feae87b5b98d6096f334a8aad350bc5d8312cee3cc9f5a6d6ea8­title: mktemp‘ЁExamplesЪwMake a temporary file with the given suffix in the system temp directory.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mktemp --suffix .txt
/tmp/tmp.lekjbhelyx.txt

```
Make a temporary file named testfile.XXX with the 'X's as random characters in the current working directory.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mktemp testfile.XXX
<WORKING_DIR>/testfile.4kh

```
Make a temporary file with a template in the system temp directory.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mktemp -t testfile.XXX
/tmp/testfile.4kh

```
Make a temporary directory with randomly generated name in the temporary directory.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mktemp -d
/tmp/tmp.NMw9fJr8K0

```
’ђђЪ¤Title: title: mktemp
Path: Examples
Content:
Make a temporary file with the given suffix in the system temp directory.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mktemp --suffix .txt
/tmp/tmp.lekjbhelyx.txt

```
Make a temporary file named testfile.XXX with the 'X's as random characters in the current working directory.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mktemp testfile.XXX
<WORKING_DIR>/testfile.4kh

```
Make a temporary file with a template in the system temp directory.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mktemp -t testfile.XXX
/tmp/testfile.4kh

```
Make a temporary directory with randomly generated name in the temporary directory.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mktemp -d
/tmp/tmp.NMw9fJr8K0

```
